## 🧰 Overview
A responsive and accessible task manager with core features for creating, organizing, and tracking workflow. Ideal for daily planning, personal objectives, and small team coordination.

## 🚀 Key Features
- Add new tasks with title, description, deadline, and priority
- Edit task details and task state (complete / incomplete)
- Delete tasks and clear completed tasks
- Filter by status (All, Active, Completed)
- Search tasks in real time
- Persist tasks in local browser storage
- Responsive UI for mobile/tablet/desktop

## 📁 Project Structure
- `index.html`: Main application markup
- `styles.css`: Styling and visual layout
- `script.js`: Application logic and behavior
- `README`: Project documentation

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- HTML5
- CSS3 (Flexbox/Grid)
- Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+)

---

## ⚙️ Installation
1. Clone repo
   - `git clone https://github.com/yourusername/task-manager-app.git`
2. Enter folder
   - `cd task-manager-app`
3. (Optional) Install dependencies if setup with packages
   - `npm install`
4. Launch app
   - `npm start` (if using a local dev server)
   - or open `index.html` in browser

## ▶️ Usage
- Add tasks with required fields
- Click task text to toggle completed state
- Use priority filter to highlight must-do items
- Use search box to find tasks instantly

---

## 🧩 Configuration
No dedicated config required for local usage. LocalStorage is used to keep data across browser sessions.

